# A function to create subsets of the original trining set
# A function to create subsets of the original trining set
import numpy as np
import math
def generate_test_training(feat_matrix):
    ''' Generates test and training set from a feature matrix + labels / target var
    assuming labels / target var in the last column with 90/10'''
    feat_matrix_reindex = feat_matrix.reindex(np.random.permutation(feat_matrix.index))
    columns = feat_matrix_reindex.columns
    train_x = feat_matrix_reindex[columns[:-1]]
    train_y = feat_matrix_reindex[columns[len(feat_matrix_reindex.columns)-1]]
    num_rows_train = int(math.modf(.9 * len(train_x))[1])
    X_train = train_x[:int(num_rows_train)]
    y_train = train_y[:int(num_rows_train)]
    X_test =  train_x[int(num_rows_train):]
    y_test =  train_y[int(num_rows_train):]
    return X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test

def get_dummy(DataFrame):
    columns = ( 'companyId', 'jobType', 'degree','major', 'industry')
    transformed_df = DataFrame
    for ed_elem in columns:
        if ed_elem in transformed_df.columns:
            dummy = pd.get_dummies(transformed_df[ed_elem], prefix=ed_elem)
            del transformed_df[ed_elem]
            # Drop the old column
            transformed_df =  pd.merge(transformed_df, dummy, left_index=True, right_index=True)
    return transformed_df
